        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>mezzotint (process) [300053233], engraving (printing process) [300053225], intaglio printing processes [300199636], printing processes [300199635], printing and printing processes and techniques [300185289], image-making processes and techniques [300053159], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A printing process developed in the 20th century in which mezzotint-like tone is achieved by roughening the surface of the plate with abrasives. The process was developed as a way to avoid the laborious process of rocking the plate.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000016051/Gascoigne, How to Identify Prints (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een in de 20e eeuw ontwikkeld drukprocedé waarbij de mezzotint-achtige schakering wordt bereikt door het oppervlak van de plaat met schuurmiddelen op te ruwen. Het procedé werd ontwikkeld als een manier om het arbeidsintensieve plaatschommelen te omzeilen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>發展於二十世紀的印刷技法，利用研磨材料磨擦印版表面，製作出類似美柔汀的調子。此一技法的發展，可省去費力搖磨印版的程序。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
